3.Â Exception Handling:
 try-catch-finally
Â The try block is used to specify a block of code that may throw an exception. The catch block is used to handle the exception if it is thrown. The finally block is used to execute the code after the try and catch blocks have been executed.
Â 
try {
Â Â Â Â int result = 10 / 0;
} catch (ArithmeticException e) {
Â Â Â Â System.out.println("Cannot divide by zero!");
} finally {
Â Â Â Â System.out.println("This block always runs.");
}
Â·Â 
try: Contains risky code.
Â·Â 
Â·Â 
catch: Handles exceptions.
Â·Â 
Â·Â 
finally: Executes regardless of exception.
Â·Â 



5. Method Overloading vs Overriding
