14. How Many Ways Can We Create a String Object?

âœ… Two Ways to Create Strings in Java
1ï¸âƒ£ Using String Literals
* Stored in String Constant Pool (SCP)
String str1 = "Hello";
ğŸ”¹ This is memory-efficient because identical literals point to the same SCP reference.

2ï¸âƒ£ Using the new Keyword
* Stored in Heap Memory
* If interned, also stored in SCP
String str2 = new String("Hello");
ğŸ”¹ This always creates a new object in the heap, even if the string value already exists in the SCP.

ğŸ’¡ Interview Tip: â€¨String literals save memory by using the String Constant Pool, where identical strings share the same reference.

