24. How to Convert String to Array and Use It
âœ… How to Convert a String to an Array in Java â€” with Simple Examples
There are 3 common types of conversions:

ğŸ”¹ 1. String to Character Array (char[])
String str = "Java";
char[] charArray = str.toCharArray();

for (char ch : charArray) {
    System.out.println(ch);
}
ğŸ”¸ Use when: You want to work on each character separately.

ğŸ”¹ 2. String to String Array using .split()
String str = "Java is awesome";
String[] words = str.split(" ");  // Split by space

for (String word : words) {
    System.out.println(word);
}
ğŸ”¸ Use when: You want to break the string by words, comma, or any delimiter.
String csv = "apple,banana,grape";
String[] fruits = csv.split(",");

ğŸ”¹ 3. Convert String of Numbers to Integer Array
String str = "1,2,3,4,5";
String[] parts = str.split(",");
int[] numbers = new int[parts.length];

for (int i = 0; i < parts.length; i++) {
    numbers[i] = Integer.parseInt(parts[i]);
}
ğŸ”¸ Use when: You want to process numbers stored as a string.

ğŸ§  Bonus: Convert Character Array Back to String
char[] arr = {'J', 'a', 'v', 'a'};
String str = new String(arr);
System.out.println(str);  // Output: Java

âœ… Summary Table
Task	Code Example
String â†’ char[]	str.toCharArray()
String â†’ String[] (words)	str.split(" ")
CSV â†’ int[]	Integer.parseInt(str.split(","))
char[] â†’ String	new String(charArray)
