6. If we initialize DateÂ class object in a singleton, will the DateÂ object be singleton too?
Â·Â 
No. The DateÂ object inside singleton is just a field. Unless you make DateÂ immutable and prevent modification, each call to its methods can change internal state.
Â·Â 
Â·Â 
Singleton guarantees a single instance of the class, not its mutable fields.
Â·Â 



